snPortCARTable.name: snPortCARTable
snPortCARTable.description: A table of rate limit configuration entries. Rate Limit is a method of traffic control. It allows a set of rate limits to be configured and applied to packets flowing into/out of an interface to regulate network traffic.

snPortCAREntry.name: snPortCAREntry
snPortCAREntry.description: A collection of rate-limit configuration objects on this interface.

snPortCARifIndex.name: snPortCARifIndex
snPortCARifIndex.description: The ifIndex value for this rate limit entry.

snPortCARDirection.name: snPortCARDirection
snPortCARDirection.description: The input or output transmission direction for the Rate Limit object. input (0), --for inbound traffic output(1) --for outbound traffic

snPortCARRowIndex.name: snPortCARRowIndex
snPortCARRowIndex.description: The table index for rate limit objects. It increases as the rate limit entries are added. Skips the number when a row is deleted.

snPortCARType.name: snPortCARType
snPortCARType.description: The type of traffic rate-limited against.

snPortCARAccIdx.name: snPortCARAccIdx
snPortCARAccIdx.description: The index to the access list if RateLimitType is either quickAcc or standardAcc.

snPortCARRate.name: snPortCARRate
snPortCARRate.description: The comitted access rate. This determines the long term average transmission rate. Traffic that falls under this rate always conforms. This is average rate in bits per second.

snPortCARLimit.name: snPortCARLimit
snPortCARLimit.description: This is the normal burst size that determines how large traffic bursts can be before some traffic exceeds the rate limit. This specifies the number of bytes that are guaranteed to be transported by the network at the average rate under normal conditions during committed time interval. This normal burst size is in bytes.

snPortCARExtLimit.name: snPortCARExtLimit
snPortCARExtLimit.description: This is the extended burst limit that determines how large traffic bursts can be before all the traffic exceeds the rate limit. This burst size is in bytes.

snPortCARConformAction.name: snPortCARConformAction
snPortCARConformAction.description: Action to be taken when the traffic is within the Rate Limit. drop drop the packet. xmit transmit the packet. continue continue to evaluate to the subsequent rate limits. precedXmit rewrite the IP precedence and transmit the packet. precedCont rewrite the IP precedence and allow it evaluated by subsequent rate limits.

snPortCARExceedAction.name: snPortCARExceedAction
snPortCARExceedAction.description: Action to be taken when the traffic exceeds the Rate Limit.drop drop the packet. xmit transmit the packet. continue continue to evaluate to the subsequent rate limits. precedXmit rewrite the IP precedence and transmit the packet. precedCont rewrite the IP precedence and allow it evaluated by subsequent rate limits.

snPortCARStatSwitchedPkts.name: snPortCARStatSwitchedPkts
snPortCARStatSwitchedPkts.description: The counter of packets permitted by this rate limit.

snPortCARStatSwitchedBytes.name: snPortCARStatSwitchedBytes
snPortCARStatSwitchedBytes.description: The counter of bytes permitted by this interface.

snPortCARStatFilteredPkts.name: snPortCARStatFilteredPkts
snPortCARStatFilteredPkts.description: The counter of packets which exceeded this rate limit.

snPortCARStatFilteredBytes.name: snPortCARStatFilteredBytes
snPortCARStatFilteredBytes.description: The counter of bytes which exceeded this rate limit.
